The paper focuses on depth estimation for light field photography, which is a computer vision problem, suggesting that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also mentions analyzing the geometry of scene structures, which falls under graphics (cs.GR). The use of superpixels and regularization techniques suggests that the paper may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper proposes a new framework for depth estimation, which involves manipulating weights, indicating that it may also be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
